 {"id":"franken_networkx-5e8p","title":"parity: subgraph should return frozen views across graph classes","description":"Graph, DiGraph, MultiGraph, and MultiDiGraph currently return mutable graph copies from subgraph(...), while upstream NetworkX returns frozen induced-subgraph views. In FrankenNetworkX, H = G.subgraph([...]) allows H.add_node('z') and succeeds; in NetworkX the same call raises NetworkXError('Frozen graph can't be modified'). Match the upstream frozen-view contract across the core graph classes.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T07:56:19.830339850Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T07:58:03.930423597Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
